Visualization: Case 2- Objective Implement predictive maintenance to maximize efficiency in older, high-output plants. 6
Positive Insight:
Plants over 21+ years old (with an Avg Plant Age 45 years) still maintain a significant average capacity. These plants remain productive even at an advanced age, ensuring continuous power generation despite their age.



Negative Insight:
There is a direct relationship between age and maintenance needs. Older plants (21+ years) require more maintenance, which results in higher operational costs. You can see the correlation in the chart, where higher maintenance needs are observed for older plants.




Case 2 ROI:
By focusing on predictive maintenance, we can extend the lifespan of these older plants, leading to $14.6M in annual savings by preventing costly emergency repairs and reducing downtime. The Average Plant Age and KPI Breakdown sections demonstrate how maintenance impacts plant longevity and overall performance.
